Sentencas: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+delta (PBSCCo) oxide is synthesized by EDTA-citrate complexing method and investigated as a novel cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction results show that PBSCCo is chemical compatible with Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte below 950 degrees
Titulo: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient of PBSCCo is 17.58 x 10 (6) K (1) between 30 degrees C and 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum electrical conductivity of PBSCCo is 483 S cm (1) at 325 degrees
Titulo: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of PBSCCo cathode on GDC electrolyte is as low as 0.06 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the electrolyte-supported single cell with PBSCCo cathode achieves 521 mWcm (2) at 800 degrees C. Preliminary results indicate that PBSCCo is a potential cathode material for application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Layered perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5CoCuO5+δ as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
